</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AD80FC68E3B5C87B58FEB6B224667" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5886D6886CC038B7B139F36EF7DD5233" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0BAE37F6D26E5A30C7B33B926C9C95AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="0A693A2562BBB7F1306A61CC8F2EEFA3" authorityName="Rakotonirina &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus karsti" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karsti">
<emphasis id="0F7E19D5C2317226224F11483393C44F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Camponotus karsti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confounded with 
<taxonomicName id="02CA0666B3D56E082CFF86E908903488" genus="C." lsidName="C. harenarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="harenarum">
<emphasis id="88714743370CFF7E3DB9FDBA9F3E6177" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. harenarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because both species are characterized by the presence of a blunt angle at approximately the posterior 1/2 of propodeal dorsum. However, 
<taxonomicName id="9867710D2285B6F201CE6229386EFB76" genus="C." lsidName="C. harenarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="harenarum">
<emphasis id="DB6316E7440640D931B7A88960F4AB8C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. harenarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the separate convexity of its mesonotum and anterior 1/2 of propodeum, and its petiolar node is approximately as high as long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5F4D09D62083BE44436F29BD772B2FED" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5848039A6A9C0FA8688305392831068F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F87A8613D53DBEA05B17B8F51DE056E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species name 
<taxonomicName id="2C28BCE99B7F73F15A1308F67484C649" authorityName="Rakotonirina &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus karsti" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karsti">
<emphasis id="12E2905398C086095188A3E065D4CA33" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Camponotus karsti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a non-Latin singular noun used in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
